OIL, SECONDARY (OIS)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Maynard Oil Co. said it agreed to pay $13.7
million for Sun Operating Limited Partnership's interest in
five leases covering 860 surface acres of the Levelland Field
in Hockley County, Texas. Maynard estimated the acquisition
would add 525 net barrels to its daily production. Sun
Operating is managed by Oryx Energy Co. of Dallas, which, as
managing general partner, has a 98% ownership of the limited
partnership.
