   TOKYO -- Japan's Fuji Heavy Industries Ltd., the maker of
Subaru automobiles, said it received approval from the U.S.
Securities and Exchange Commission to seek a 100% stake in
its U.S. sales subsidiary, Subaru of America.
   A special shareholders meeting will be held Aug. 27 to
consider terms for the buy-out, a spokesman said. He added
that no final decision has been made on what price Fuji Heavy
Industries will offer for the shares outstanding.
