   Veba AG of West Germany, a diversified energy and trading
company, reported that first-half group net income slipped
1.5% to 391 million marks ($250.2 million) from 397 million
marks a year earlier.
   The company said the results were dragged down by the
petroleum and chemical sectors, where earnings declined from
