   If all necessary approvals are met, Worthen, based in
Little Rock, Ark., said it expects closing on or before Dec.
31. Worthen said the acquisition price would depend upon the
earnings of Twin City and TC Bankshares, both Arkansas-based
banking concerns, but will not exceed $75 million if closing
occurs by Dec. 31. If the closing occurs after that date, the
purchase price could exceed $75 million, depending on the two
firms' earnings, Worthen said.
