   PITTSBURGH -- Consolidated Natural Gas Co. said its CNG
Transmission Corp. unit reached a consent agreement with the
state to locate and clean up contamination from its
Pennsylvania gas pipeline.
   A company spokesman estimated CNG Transmission would pay
$900,000 for the initial search for contamination.
</LP>
