<LP>
   DENVER -- Forest Oil Corp. said it discovered natural gas
offshore Louisiana on West Delta Block 20.
   The well flowed at a rate of 7.4 million cubic feet of gas
per day through a 17/64 inch choke at a depth of 16,849 feet.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Forest Oil, with a 50% interest, drilled the well, but
Wainoco Oil &amp; Gas Co., with a 33.33% interest will operate
the well. Newfield Exploration Co. holds a 16.67% interest.
